CLOSTRIDIUM PERFRINGENS & REPEATED GI OUTBREAKS (2)
===================================================
[This posting collects 2 replies to the RFI, which
reported cases of gastrointestinal disease over an extended
period, and inquired about a potential role for Clostridium
perfringens. - Mod.]

[1]
From: Robert Savage <RSAVAGE@CI.MADISON.WI.US>
Date: Fri, 19 Jan 1996 13:18:05 -0600
There are several excellent resources re: foodborne illness.
The FDA has a web page at:
http://vm.cfsan.fda.gov/list.html
A good text with reference to many bacterial illnesses, including
Clostridium perfringens:
Bacterial Infections of Humans:epidemiology and control--2nd ed
ed. by Alfred Evans and Philip Brachman
Plenum Medical Book Co
1991
An outbreak of Clostridium perfringens that lasted a month would be
unusual in my experience. It would require consistently poor
foodhandling practices.
--
Rob Savage
Communicable Disease Epidemiologist
Madison Department of Public Health
Madison, Wisconsin, USA
e-mail: RSAVAGE@CI.MADISON.WI.US
